The paper discusses a method for localizing users in large-scale MIMO systems, which involves processing signals obtained from distributed base stations. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed method also involves exploiting channel properties to distinguish LOS from non-LOS signal paths, which is related to system and control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions using compressed sensing, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV).
